-- Venezuela Says Saudi Arabian Drilling Rig Songa Saturno Arrives Next Week
-- B y   J o s e   O r o z c o
-- 2010-09-24T05:31:41Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-24/venezuela-says-saudi-arabian-drilling-rig-songa-saturno-arrives-next-week.html
Petroleos de Venezuela SA, the
state oil company, said the $2.5 billion Songa Saturno offshore
platform leased from Petrosaudi Oil Services Ltd. will arrive in
the South American country Sept. 28.  Petrosaudiâ€™s Songa Saturno platform, which will be used to
develop offshore natural-gas resources, joins the Petrosaudi
Discover rig in replacing the Aban Pearl platform that sank near
Trinidad and Tobago in May, Oil and Energy Minister Rafael
Ramirez said, according to a company statement sent by e-mail
late last night.   A PDVSA-Petrosaudi venture, where the Venezuelan company
would have a majority stake, will eventually purchase the two
rigs, the statement said, citing Ramirez. The $2.5 billion
investment for the Songa Saturno rig covers a five-year period,
the statement said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
